CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 2, 1954, pg. 11, reads: "Junior Leaguers Party - The Junior Leaguers, gay sub-debs, gathered in playroom of Knott Manor, Tuesday, Dec. 29, to have their holiday party. Pictured are, from left to right, first row: Joan Hobson, Kay Stokes, Beverly Butler, Joyce Robins, Sarah Burney, Boots Bray.  Second row: Carol Jones, Gay Cyrus, Joanne Vanderhoop, Marva Jo Hord, Sylvia Knott, Roberta Ratcliffe, and Betsy Johnson, having a good time.
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of thirteen young women from Junior League, seated on stools from left: Joan Hobson, Kay Stokes, Beverly Butler, Joyce Robins, Sarah Burney, LouJeanne "Bootsie" Bray; standing: Carol Jones, Gay Cyrus, Joanne Vanderhoop, Marva Jo Hord, Sylvia Knott, Roberta Ratcliffe, and Betsy Johnson, posed in playroom of Knott Manor, another version
